==Latin==
===Etymology===
Both words are from Latin '''[[mutare]]''', ''change''.  '''Mutatis''' is the ablative plural of the perfect passive participle, and '''mutandis''' is the ablative plural of the future passive participle or gerundive.

===Adverb===
{{wikipedia}}
'''mutatis mutandis'''

# Literally ''"those things having been changed which were to be changed"''; having [[change]]d what needed to be changed.

